In January, Federer withdrew from the 2021 Australian Open due to still recovering from his knee surgery and strict COVID-19 quarantine measures in Australia.[258][259] On 8 March, Novak Djokovic moved past him for the highest number of career weeks spent as the ATP number 1 ranked player.[260]. On 10 March, he made his return to the ATP Tour at the Qatar Open. He won his first ATP match in 14 months against Dan Evans, but lost to Nikoloz Basilashvili in the next round.[261]
